The paper proposes a regularization method for fine-tuning pre-trained deep networks for the task of k-shot learning, which involves training a model with limited data. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and specifically involves convolutional neural networks (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of reinforcement learning (cs.AI) and recurrent networks (cs.NE) for optimizing the grouping of neurons. Finally, the paper deals with classification tasks (cs.CL) using deep networks.
